HEADWORD: Hobblebush
<hw>Hob"ble*bush`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Bot.)</fld>
<def>A low bush (<spn>Viburnum lantanoides</spn>) having long,
straggling branches and handsome flowers. It is found in the Northern
United States. Called also <altname>shinhopple</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

